Mr Akinropo Oparinde, 41, on Monday appeared before an Iyaganku Magistratesâ€™ Court in Ibadan, for allegedly collecting N1.1 million to procure a Spanish Visa for one Gabriel Ademuyiwa. Oparinde faces a three-count charge of conspiracy, obtaining money under false pretence and stealing.
He pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Prosecutor, Insp. Sikiru Opaleye told the court that the defendant committed the offence in March 2021 at Ologuneru area of Ibadan. Opaleye said the defendant and others at large allegedly collected the money from Ademuyiwa, knowing that it was false. He said he committed an offence contrary to and punishable under Section 516, 419 and 390 of the Criminal Law of Oyo State, 2000. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs Olabisi Ogunkanmi, granted the defendant bail to the tune of half-a-million naira and two sureties in like sum. The case was later adjourned to March 28 for hearing.